[CODE EFFICIENCY]

Component rules:
- If a UI pattern repeats more than twice, extract it into a reusable component
- Props must be typed with an explicit interface, never inline type
- Default props must be defined in the function signature, not separately
- Keep each component file under 150 lines. If it exceeds this, split it

Conditional rendering:
- Use early return for guard conditions instead of deeply nested ternaries
- Maximum ternary depth: 1. Use if statements or separate variables for complex logic

Class names:
- Never repeat the same Tailwind class combination more than twice in one file
- If a class combination is reused, extract it into a const variable at the top of the file
- Example: const cardClass = "bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6"

Data fetching:
- Never fetch the same data twice on one page
- Pass data down as props, do not re-fetch in child components
- Use React cache() for server-side deduplication if the same query is needed in multiple server components

Imports:
- Group imports in this order: React, Next.js, third party libraries, internal components, types, utils
- Use absolute imports from the project root, never use relative paths like ../../components

