[NAMING CONVENTION]

Files and folders:
- React components: PascalCase — example: TransactionList.tsx
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix — example: useTransactions.ts
- Server actions: camelCase — example: createTransaction.ts
- Utility functions: camelCase — example: formatCurrency.ts
- Types and interfaces: PascalCase — example: Transaction, CategoryType
- SQL migration files: numbered prefix — example: 001_create_categories.sql
- Folders: lowercase with dash — example: /lib/supabase, /lib/actions

Variables and functions:
- Boolean variables: prefix with is, has, or can — example: isLoading, hasError, canDelete
- Event handlers: prefix with handle — example: handleSubmit, handleDelete
- Server actions: prefix with verb — example: createTransaction, updateCategory, deleteTransaction
- Fetcher functions in hooks: prefix with fetch — example: fetchTransactions, fetchCategories
- Type for component props: suffix with Props — example: TransactionListProps, ButtonProps

Constants:
- All caps with underscore — example: DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE, MAX_BUDGET_LIMIT
- Define at the top of the file or in /lib/utils/constants.ts if shared across files

