[SERVER ACTION RESPONSE PATTERN]

All server actions must return a consistent response object. Never throw errors directly to the client.

Return type structure:
- Success: { success: true, data: T }
- Error: { success: false, error: string }

Example pattern:
export async function createTransaction(payload: CreateTransactionPayload) {
  try {
    // validate session first
    // perform database operation
    return { success: true, data: result }
  } catch (err) {
    return { success: false, error: "Failed to create transaction. Please try again." }
  }
}

Client side handling:
- Always check result.success before proceeding
- If success is false, show the error message via toast
- If success is true, show success toast and refresh data
- Never expose raw database error messages to the user
- Error messages shown to user must be human readable, not technical

