[SUPABASE RLS POLICY]

Row Level Security must be enabled on every table. Never create a table without RLS.

Rules:
- Always enable RLS immediately after creating a table: ALTER TABLE table_name ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
- Every table must have at minimum these four policies: select, insert, update, delete for authenticated users
- All policies must filter by auth.uid() = user_id
- Never create a policy with USING (true) or WITH CHECK (true) unless I explicitly ask
- Service role key must never be used in client-side code

Standard policy pattern for every table:
CREATE POLICY "Users can view own data" ON table_name
  FOR SELECT USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can insert own data" ON table_name
  FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can update own data" ON table_name
  FOR UPDATE USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can delete own data" ON table_name
  FOR DELETE USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

Always include these four policies in every migration file that creates a table.

