[ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES]

Use exactly these variable names in all code. Never invent new names.

.env.local structure:
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

Rules:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL — used in both client and server
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY — used in both client and server
- Never use SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in any client-side code
- Never hardcode any URL or key value directly in code
- Always access via process.env.VARIABLE_NAME
- If a variable is missing, throw a descriptive error at the top of the file

Example:
const supabaseUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
if (!supabaseUrl) throw new Error("Missing NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL")